  "name": "Morrison COU2 — VAD hemolysis credibility assessment (NC-5 clean)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under ventricular assist device (VAD) conditions. COU2 evaluates whether the computational model can predict absolute hemolysis levels for a Class III VAD device at Model Risk Level 5. Twelve of thirteen credibility factors are assessed with achieved levels meeting or exceeding required levels. One factor — Equivalency of input parameters — is formally scoped-out because the FDA generic pump geometry is a canonical reference geometry with no physical test article; consequently no equivalency comparison between computational inputs and a physical specimen is possible or meaningful. Decision: Accepted with complete provenance and all credibility gaps resolved or formally scoped-out.",
